pull_request.title: Change hybrid curve numbers to use private range as recommended in Internet-Draft
pull_request.body:
Fixes #168. 

https://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-tls-hybrid-design-00 says the code points reserved for hybrid private use are `0x2F00..0x2FFF`, so this updates to use that range.  

Also changes a few recently added non-hybrid curve numbers to be sequential.

Numbers recorded in https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/12YarzaNv3XQNLnvDsWLlRKwtZFhRrDdWf36YlzwrPeg/edit?usp=sharing

pull_request.title: Increase max size for signatures in speed.c
pull_request.body:
Increases max signature sizes for speed tests to 35000 (enough for picnicl1fs). Test code is hard to read, but it uses the last value of `lengths_list` array to allocate the signature buffer in the OQS tests. We'll need to update this value as we add algs with larger sigs.

Fixes issue #159.
